definition.value: The (S)-enantiomer of 5-bromo-3-(butan-2-yl)-6-methylpyrimidine-2,4(1H,3H)-dione.
A pyrimidine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is CMP in which the 2-keto group on the cytosine ring is replaced by an epsilon-L-lysyl residue.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is CMP(2-) in which the 2-keto group on the cytosine ring is substituted by an epsilon-L-lysyl residue. Major structure at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v. 6.2.0).

An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of 3-(p-tert-butylphenyl)-3-(6-chloropyridin-2-yl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine. A fungicide developed in China, it shows high antifungal activity against diseases caused by Phytophthora infestans, Phytophthora capsici, Rhizoctonia solani, Peronophythora litchi, and Pseudoperonospora cubensis.
A nucleotide residue derived from lysine monophosphate.
A zwitterionic group that is the major structure at pH 7.3 of lysidine monophosphate residue (according to Marvin v. 6.2.0).
A 1-{2-[(2,6-dichlorobenzyl)oxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (R)-enantiomer of isoconazole.
A member of the class of imidazoles that carries a 2-[(2,6-dichlorobenzyl)oxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl group at position 1.
A 1-{2-[(2,6-dichlorobenzyl)oxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of isoconazole.
An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (R)-isoconazole and nitric acid.
A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 9-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (S)-isoconazole and nitric acid.
A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 5-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (S)-isoconazole.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (R)-isoconazole.
A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 10-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 11-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 13-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by a (2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino group at postion 2.
A member of the class of chromenes that is 2H-chromene substituted by a methoxy group at position 7 and two methyl groups at position 2.
The (R)-enantiomer of  2-[(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino]-2-oxoethanesulfonic acid.
The (S)-enantiomer of  2-[(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino]-2-oxoethanesulfonic acid.
A member of the class of imidazoles that carries a 2-[(7-chloro-1-benzothiophen-3-yl)methoxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl group at position 1.
An N-terminal alpha-amino-acid residue derived from N-terminal N-acetyl-L-alanine.
A 1-{2-[(7-chloro-1-benzothiophen-3-yl)methoxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of sertaconazole.

A 1-{2-[(7-chloro-1-benzothiophen-3-yl)methoxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the active R-enantiomer of sertaconazole and is used (as its nitrate salt) for treatment of vulvovaginal candidiasis. The racemate itself is also used as a broad-spectrum antifungal drug.

A member of the class of pyrimidines that is pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol in which one of the hydrogens attached to the carbon bearing the hydroxy group is replaced by a 2-chlorophenyl group while the other is replaced by a 4-chlorophenyl group.

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-sertaconazole nitrate. A broad spectrum antifungal with added antipruritic and anti-inflammatory activity used for treatment of various skin infections.
A (2-chlorophenyl)(4-chlorophenyl)pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol that has R configuration.
A (2-chlorophenyl)(4-chlorophenyl)pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol that has S configuration.
An N-terminal alpha-amino-acid residue derived from N-terminal N-acetyl-L-serine.
An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of (S)-sertaconazole and nitric acid.

An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of equimolar amounts of arasertaconazole and nitric acid. The active R-enantiomer of sertaconazole nitrate that is used for treatment of vulvovaginal candidiasis. The racemate itself is also used as a broad-spectrum antifungal drug.
A (2-chlorophenyl)(4-fluorophenyl)pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol that has R configuration.
A (2-chlorophenyl)(4-fluorophenyl)pyrimidin-5-ylmethanol that has S configuration.
A synthetic 25-membered heterodetic cyclic peptide consisting of a 14-membered linear component attached to an 11-membered cyclic portion. A CK2 inhibitor with potential antineoplastic activity.
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from any N(5)-alkyl-L-glutamine.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the imidazole group of (S)-sertaconazole
A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 7-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 8-PAHSA, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

A monothioglycerolipid in which the parent monothioglycerol is esterified on O-1 and O-2 by stearoyl groups and on S-3 by a 2-[(2-{beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)-[beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-1-O-yl}ethyl)amino]-2-oxoethyl group
Any member of the group of lipids containing a common monothioglycerol backbone to which at least one fatty acyl group is esterified.
A glycophytoceramide having an alpha-D-Gal-(1->2)alpha-DGal glycosyl group at the O-1 position and a hexacosanoyl group attached to the nitrogen.
A sphingoid that is the C14-analogue of sphingosine.

A tertiary alcohol that is ethanol in which one of the hydrogens at position 1 is replaced by an p-fluorophenyl group, the other hydrogen at position 1 is replaced by a p-fluorophenyl group, and one of the hydrogens at position 2 is replaced by a 1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl group.
A 1-(2-fluorophenyl)-1-(4-fluorophenyl)-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)ethanol that has R configuration.
